-- Czech Stocks: Central European Media, CEZ Are Active in Prague
-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 2011-12-15T11:23:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-15/czech-stocks-central-european-media-cez-are-active-in-prague.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX stock index (PX) 
retreated 0.3 percent to 851.3 at 12:05 p.m. in Prague.  The following were among the most active equities on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Central European Media Enterprises Ltd. (CETV CP) fell a
second day, retreating 1.6 to 142.1 koruna in Prague. The
broadcaster is “catching up with losses from the yesterday’s
close in the U.S. where it was dragged down by the market,”
said J&T analyst Pavel Ryska by phone. The company’s U.S.-traded
shares plunged 6.1 percent yesterday.  CEZ AS (CEZ)  , the country’s biggest power producer,
declined a second day, sliding 0.4 percent to 747.16 koruna.
Electricity for next-year delivery in  Germany , where
the company exports part of its output, fell for a fourth day.  To contact the reporter on this story:
